The Hungarian government will
increase the capital of state-owned airline Malev Zrt. by 2.5
billion forint ($13.3 million), to ensure the short-term
financing of the unprofitable carrier,  MTI  news service
reported, citing MNV, the government asset manager.  The capital increase will take place by April 7, according
to MTI.  To contact the reporter on this story:
